      <bioghist>
         <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
         <p>Dr. Raymond J. Garbutt was the chief veterinarian of the American Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals in New York City in the 1920s. </p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Writings, scrapbooks, photographs and lantern slides from Dr. Raymond J. Garbutt, DMV. The collection pertains to his his career as a small animal practitioner and his work at the American Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals. </p>
      </scopecontent>
